jQuery hasClass()
The jQuery hasClass() method is used to check whether selected elements have specified class name or not. 
It returns TRUE if the specified class is present in any of the selected elements otherwise it returns FALSE.

---------------

<!DOCTYPE html>  
<html>  
<head>  
<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.3/jquery.min.js"></script>  
<script>  
$(document).ready(function(){  
    $("button").click(function(){  
        alert($("p").hasClass("intro"));  
    });  
});  
</script>  
<style>  
.intro {  
    font-size: 150%;  
    color: Blue;  
}  
</style>  
</head>  
<body>  
<h1>Look here, I am a heading.</h1>  
<p class="intro">This is a paragraph.</p>  
<p>This is also a paragraph.</p>  
<button>Click here to check if any p element have an "intro" class?</button>  
</body>  
</html>  

 
